## Quick Start

```bash
# Start daemon
bir daemon start

# Analyze a page
bir explain https://example.com

# Click element by ref
bir click @e5

# Compare versions
bir diff compare v1.json v2.json
```

## Workflow

1. Start daemon: `bir daemon start`
2. Analyze page: `bir explain <url>`
3. Interact using refs: `bir click @e5`
4. Use memory: `bir memory store/recall`
5. Compare versions: `bir diff compare`
6. Self-healing: `bir heal.find`
7. Multi-browser: `bir multi.*`
8. Agent coordination: `bir agent.*`

## Tips

1. Always start with `bir explain` ‚Äî get the IR before any action
2. Use refs, not CSS ‚Äî `@e5` is deterministic, CSS selectors break
3. Check intent ‚Äî understand what the page is for
4. Check risks ‚Äî BrowserIR warns about destructive actions
5. Use memory ‚Äî store and recall patterns
6. Use flow ‚Äî detect multi-step processes
7. Use diff ‚Äî compare page versions
8. Use heal ‚Äî fix broken selectors automatically
9. Use multi ‚Äî test across multiple tabs
10. Use agent ‚Äî coordinate multiple AI agents
